overview: >-
  The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with issues,
  including critical security flaws, functional bugs, and failing Vercel
  deployments. The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the PR comments and CI
  logs, identifying insecure authentication, arbitrary API parameter acceptance,
  memory-intensive CSV exports, PDF generation errors (NaNs, missing minutes,
  hardcoded names), and missing input validations.

  The agent systematically addressed these by implementing HMAC-signed session
  tokens, adding pagination and limits to API routes and CSV exports, rewriting
  PDF metric calculations for accuracy, enabling null inputs for number fields,
  and integrating a PDF download button. Time input validation was also enhanced
  with regex.

  A key challenge emerged with Vercel's Edge Runtime, as the initial secure
  authentication used Node.js , incompatible with the Edge environment.
  The agent proactively refactored the authentication logic to leverage the Web
  Crypto API, ensuring compatibility. While local builds and GitHub Actions
  passed, Vercel deploys continued to fail, indicating further Vercel-specific
  configuration issues that the agent began to investigate.
